cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE 

The paper analyzes three large datasets of computer science papers in the categories of artificial intelligence, software engineering, and theory and methods. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as cs.AI, cs.SE, and cs.TH. Additionally, the paper applies 12 different ranking methods to the citation networks of authors, which could be related to sub-categories such as cs.DL (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DB (Databases).
